0.body: SHARP (SHARed Prover) is a powerful system designed to generate aggregated STARK proofs for multiple Cairo programs, amortizing the cost of all programs proven across a single proof. This book is structured as follows: The first chapter focuses on using SHARP, without necessarily understanding its inner workings The second chapter focuses on SHARP's architecture, in the hope of sheding some light on this boldly carved but dimly lit tunnel.
0.title: Introduction

1.body: Luckily, you don't need to understand SHARP's architecture to use it (but it's highly recommended nonetheless!) and this chapter details the ways in which you can do so: Chapter 1.1 focuses on the SHARP gateway, which is used for all interactions with SHARP Chapter 1.2 focuses on cairo-sharp, which gives free but limited access to the SHARP gateway Chapter 1.3 focuses on making Cairo PIEs, which are required by SHARP for proving Cairo programs (but don't worry, you don't have to know what these are either)
1.title: Usage

NOTE: cairo-sharp submit is rate-limited to prevent a DOS attack on SHARP. Description: Submits a Cairo PIE to be proven and verified on Sepolia. Parameters: cairo_pie: The Cairo PIE Example: $ cairo-sharp submit pie.zip Compiling...

Submitting to SHARP...
Job sent.
Job key: 699bf741-7c91-4b93-a158-aaddac7534c1s

10.title: submit

11.body: Description: Gets that status of a job submitted by cairo-sharp submit. Parameters: job_key: The key of a job submitted by cairo-sharp submit Example: $ cairo-sharp status 699bf741-7c91-4b93-a158-aaddac7534c1 PROCESSED

12.body:
Description: Checks if a job submitted by cairo-sharp submit has been verified on Sepolia. Parameters: fact: The fact of a job submitted by cairo-sharp submit node_url: An Ethereum node url Example: $ cairo-sharp is_verified 0xca15503f02f8406b599cb220879e842394f5cf2cef753f3ee430647b5981b782 \
--node_url https://ethereum-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com True
12.title: is_verified

13.body: Making a Cairo PIE is much easier than making a real pie, as demonstrated by the following steps: Install Scarb : curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://docs.swmansion.com/scarb/install.sh | sh Create a new Cairo project: scarb new cairo_pie_example cd cairo_pie_example Add the following to your project's Scarb.toml: [cairo] enable-gas = false Compile your project: scarb build Install cairo-vm/cairo1-run : git clone https://github.com/lambdaclass/cairo-vm.git cd cairo-vm/cairo1-run make deps Generate your project's Cairo PIE: cargo run ../../target/dev/cairo_pie_example.sierra.json \ --append_return_values \ --layout=small \ --cairo_pie_output=pie.zip Bon appÃ©tit! ðŸ¥§
